---
import SitePage from '../../layouts/SitePage.astro'
import signingData from '../../data/signing.json'
---

<SitePage
  title="Code Signing — PAI"
  description="Authenticode signing transparency for PAI's PowerShell flashers."
>
  <section class="signing">
    <h1>Code Signing Transparency</h1>

    <p class="banner">
      <strong>Status: not yet signed.</strong> PAI's PowerShell flashers
      (<code>flash.ps1</code>) are <em>not</em> Authenticode-signed in v0.1.0.
      This page documents our commitment to signing and will be populated with
      live certificate data and per-release signatures once our
      <a href="https://signpath.io" rel="noopener noreferrer">SignPath</a>
      application is approved. Target: v0.2.
    </p>

    <p>
      The public one-liner <code>irm https://pai.direct/flash.ps1 | iex</code>
      works today because piped input bypasses Windows' ExecutionPolicy. Users
      who save the script to disk and run it under <code>AllSigned</code> or
      <code>RemoteSigned</code> will currently see a signature failure — sign
      your own copy locally, or use the one-liner, until signing ships.
    </p>

    <h2>Planned signing certificate</h2>

    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th>Publisher</th>
          <td>{signingData.publisher || '(pending — SignPath application in review)'}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Thumbprint</th>
          <td><code>{signingData.thumbprint || '(not yet issued)'}</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Audit log</th>
          <td><a href={signingData.auditLogUrl} rel="noopener noreferrer">SignPath audit log</a></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Verify before running (once signing ships)</h2>

    <pre><code>$sig = Get-AuthenticodeSignature .\flash.ps1
$sig.Status                    # Must be: Valid
$sig.SignerCertificate.Subject  # Must contain: PAI</code></pre>

    <h2>Signed releases</h2>

    {signingData.releases.length === 0 ? (
      <p><em>No signed releases yet — signing is targeted for v0.2. The first signed release will appear here automatically once the SignPath application is approved and a release is cut.</em></p>
    ) : (
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Tag</th>
            <th>Timestamp</th>
            <th>Artifact</th>
            <th>SHA256</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {signingData.releases.map((release) =>
            release.artifacts.map((artifact) => (
              <tr>
                <td>{release.tag}</td>
                <td>{new Date(release.timestamp).toISOString().slice(0, 19) + 'Z'}</td>
                <td><code>{artifact.name}</code></td>
                <td><code>{artifact.sha256.slice(0, 16)}…</code></td>
              </tr>
            ))
          )}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    )}

    <h2>What if verification fails?</h2>

    <p>
      If <code>Get-AuthenticodeSignature</code> returns anything other than
      <code>Valid</code>, <strong>do not run the script</strong>. Report the issue
      at <a href="https://github.com/nirholas/pai/security/advisories">our security advisories page</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</SitePage>
